Mangala, who had also been linked with Manchester United and Chelsea, becomes the second Porto player to join City this summer following Fernando’s £12m move to the Etihad.

City needed more numbers at centre-back after injuries to Vincent Kompany and Matija Nasatasic left them short last term. Joleon Lescott also left on a free transfer to West Brom.

Mangala, who is eligible to face Newcastle at St James' Park on Sunday, is expected to form a centre-back partnership with captain Kompany, but admitted the holiday period was 'too long' upon his arrival at City.

